tabase or dependent query operation misconfigured related to \"region availability\").\n\n---\n\n### Final Output (JSON)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_log_keys\": [\"Region is unavailable\", \"rpc error\", \"Error 9005 (HY000)\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"productcatalogservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"The productcatalogservice logged significant errors ('Region is unavailable') during queries. This indicates a backend issue, likely with database or partitioned region services.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Logs: \\\"failed to query product by id: Error 9005 (HY000): Region is unavailable\\\"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend\",\n      \"reason\": \"Frontend experienced RPC errors while interacting with productcatalogservice, often while retrieving product details or recommendations. Failures cascaded across customer-facing operations.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Logs: \\\"rpc error: code = Unknown desc = Error 9005 (HY000): Region is unavailable\\\" observed in GET and POST requests.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Next Steps:\nTo further isolate the root cause, proceed to:\n1. Validate productcatalogservice's region and database configurations.\n2. Investigate dependency health and consistency issues that may affect query operations (e.g., partition unavailability, network latency)."}
